# {{ project_name }} — Claude Code project rules

See @AGENTS.md for project-wide rules.

## Claude-specific supplements

- `just verify --quick` exit 0 is the only ground truth for "done" — not test
  or lint output alone. The `.claude/hooks/stop.sh` hook enforces this on
  every Stop event.
- The `.claude/hooks/post-tool-use.sh` hook runs `just lint && just typecheck`
  after every Edit/Write. Fix findings before continuing.
- Set `VERIFY_KIT_SKIP=1` to bypass the Stop hook for staging work-in-progress;
  record the reason in the commit message.
- Skills under `.claude/skills/verify-kit-{verify,debug,eval}/` lazy-load when
  their description matches your task.
- MCP tools (`verify`, `list_checks`, `describe`, `trace_last`, `ralph_run`,
  ...) are available once the `verify-kit` MCP server is registered in
  `.claude/settings.json`'s `mcpServers` block — see
  `.claude/settings.json.example` for the canonical entry.
- Use `bd` (beads) for any multi-step task tracking — never inline TODO files
  or TodoWrite.
- Never read `.env`, `*.pem`, `*.key`, or credential files. `.env.example` is
  safe to read.
- Never `git add .` — always stage files individually by name.
